name: Popeye
summary: Popeyes, a popular chicken restaurant, is offering a generous promotion to brighten up "Blue Monday," considered the most depressing day of the year. Across the UK, Popeyes is giving away 20,000 free chicken tenders to cheer up customers. The promotion will run on January 16th, 2023, and customers can claim their free tenders at participating Popeyes locations. Additionally, a new Popeyes restaurant is set to open in Bracknell, while the iconic characters Tintin, Popeye, and Hemingway have entered the public domain in the US.

name: Southport
summary: On January 20, 2025, a public inquiry was announced into the events of the Southport attack, in which a teenager murdered three children at a dance class. The teenager, Axel Rudakubana, had been referred to a counter-extremism scheme three times. The Home Secretary made a statement following the announcement of the public inquiry, expressing sympathy for the victims' families and pledging support for the investigation. Police have also appealed for information following a separate burglary in Southport. The MP for Southport has warned against speculating on the trial, citing the risk of having the case thrown out. The attacker's mugshot has also been released, with Sky News describing the stabbings as "savage and senseless."

name: JD Vance
summary: J.D. Vance, the "hillbilly" from Ohio, has taken the role of vice president of the United States. His rise to power aligned with the MAGA movement, and his swearing-in ceremony has been met with mixed reactions. While some praise his authenticity, others criticize his stunned appearance in Trump's official portrait. Vance's family and associates celebrated his inaugural bash, showcasing his connections within the MAGA circle. His mother attended the ceremony, demonstrating their close bond. Vance's recent meeting with China's vice president and Elon Musk underscores his growing influence. However, reports indicate that former President Trump may be considering replacing Vance with Vivek Ramaswamy in a crucial position.

name: Shaun Murphy
summary: In the 2025 Masters Snooker final, Shaun Murphy emerged victorious over Kyren Wilson with a 10-7 score at Alexandra Palace. During the tournament, Murphy made history with a record-breaking 147 break in his semi-final win against Mark Allen, which was praised by commentators despite a missed 147 attempt in an earlier match against Neil Robertson. Murphy's triumph in the final earned him a substantial prize of £350,000, the highest in the 50-year history of the Masters. Despite a valiant effort by Wilson, Murphy's victory was marked by his ability to stave off a potential comeback in the final stages of the match.

name: Panama Canal
summary: In the midst of his inauguration, former US President Donald Trump made a bold statement, asserting that the United States would "take back" the Panama Canal. However, this claim was met with a defiant response from Panama's President. The move has sparked concerns about its potential impact on Latin America, with some experts expressing worry that it could escalate tensions and hinder diplomatic relations. Despite Trump's insistence that the canal "will be American again," Panama's government maintains that it will remain under their control. Additionally, the United Nations maritime chief has stated that the canal will not be returned to the United States. China's growing presence in the region through its "Belt and Road" initiative has also raised concerns, suggesting a shift in power dynamics and a potential source of conflict.

The Mirror described the technical issue, and Rolling Stone discussed Underwood's LGBTQ+ fans' concerns. The Daily Record claimed that Underwood's career could suffer due to her performance. The Express reported that the BBC's Clive Myrie apologized for the inauguration mishap.

name: Jeff Bezos
summary: Several news articles report on the recent space-related activities of Elon Musk and Jeff Bezos. Notably, an upcoming "space showdown" between the two billionaires, with Musk's SpaceX and Bezos's Blue Origin, is highlighted. Both companies have achieved significant milestones, such as SpaceX's past successful missions and Blue Origin's recent rocket launch into orbit. However, Blue Origin's planned booster landing failed during this launch. Additionally, the articles mention the presence of tech executives, including Bezos and Zuckerberg, at Trump's inauguration. Bezos and his fiancée recently celebrated positive news, while Bezos's New Glenn rocket underwent a test flight.

name: Michelle Obama
summary: Michelle Obama will not attend the inauguration of President-elect Donald Trump next week. Sources close to the former First Lady say she "isn't one to pretend" and that her absence is a signal that she is "done with Trump." Obama's decision not to attend the inauguration follows her absence at the funeral of former President Jimmy Carter. While former Presidents Obama, Clinton, and Bush will be present at the inauguration, Michelle Obama's decision to skip the event has been widely interpreted as a snub to Trump.
